THE PILOT REPORTED THAT HE SUCCESSFULLY TOUCHED DOWN DURING CONDITIONS 
OF A RIGHT, 90 DEG. CROSSWIND. THE PILOT STATED THAT A GUST WAS THEN 
ENCOUNTERED WHICH 'WEATHER COCKED' HIS AIRCRAFT. AS HE ATTEMPTED TO 
REALIGN THE AIRCRAFT WITH THE RUNWAY THE DOWNWIND WING CONTACTED THE RUNWAY 
SURFACE AND CONTOL WAS LOST. THE AIRCRAFT VEERED OFF THE RUNWAY, NOSED OVER AND 
CAME TO REST IN A FIELD ADJACENT TO THE RUNWAY. 
